
Week 1 – Power BI Basics and Data Types

“In Week 1, I learned how to import data into Power BI from different sources like CSV files and Excel files.

I also learned about different types of data structures:

Structured data – organized data stored in tables like Excel or databases

Semi-structured data – data like JSON or XML which has some structure but not fully organized

Unstructured data – data like text, images, or videos which do not have a fixed format.

I also learned about the three main views in Power BI:

Report View – used to create visualizations like charts and dashboards

Data View – used to view the dataset in tabular format

Model View – used to understand relationships between different tables.”
